        <h1 class="text-center" style="font-style: italic; margin-top: 50px; margin-bottom: 10%"> The birth of our society</h1>
        <h3 class="text-center" style="font-style: italic; margin-top: 50px; margin-bottom: 10%">In June 2013, Matthew Pavlinovich set up a Facebook page entitled "Remember Midlands". Subsequently over a period of time a large amount of attention was generated. Because of this interest, in mid 2016 Matthew sought to arrange a gathering of those who might be interested in establishing a historical society as an Incorporated Association to focus on Midland and surrounds, but not those adjacent areas with established societies such as Guildford.
            During the latter half of 2016 a small group met informally and arising from those meetings it was decided to hold a public forum to gauge interest. The forum was held on Sunday 2 December 2016 at which around 80 people attented. Resulting from this Forum it has been assessed that it would be viable to proceed with becoming an Incorporated Association now known as the Midland and Districts Historical Society.
            The Society became an affiliated memeber of the Royal Western Australian Historical Society Inc. in August 2019.
        </h3>
